Gelechia bathrochlora is a moth of the family Gelechiidae. It is found in Brazil.The wingspan is about 9 mm. The forewings are grey suffusedly irrorated black with ochreous-white markings. There is a basal patch occupying one-fourth of the wing, enclosing a small black spot on the base of the costa, as well a small semi-oval spot on the middle of the costa and a large hemispherical tornal spot, and a small rounded spot on the costa opposite its posterior portion. The hindwings are grey.